reviewText:
Scarier, more immersive and frantic than the its top down counter part, this 3rd person version is as much fun as the original, plus the improvements of some of the DLCs. The store page is cristal clear on the content.
I have the original and I'm really enjoying this second playthrough.
-----
Edit. I was too quick to write about the game. Aiming is terrible and doesn't work at all. In the orginal version you had enough time to aim and do some headshots, in this game the aim is not assisted, i.e. the bullet or arrow goes straight were you are aiming.
Problems :
- zombies come to contact and your weapon becomes utterly useless as you CAN NOT aim at objects next to you ;
- zombies come in groups, every time you need to free a shelter they are so numerous you will inevitably die ;
- zombies spawn every few seconds ;

This is a poorly developped game.
